  "sn11.15:1.1": "Linked Discourses 11",
  "sn11.15:2.1": "2 The Second Chapter",
  "sn11.15:3.1": "15 Delightful",
  "sn11.15:4.1": "Near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove.",
  "sn11.15:4.2": "And then Sakka, the Lord of Gods, went up to the Buddha, ",
  "sn11.15:4.3": "bowed, stood to one side,",
  "sn11.15:4.4": "and said to him:",
  "sn11.15:4.5": "“Sir, what is a delightful place?”",
  "sn11.15:5.1": "“Shrines in parks and forests,",
  "sn11.15:5.2": "well-made lotus ponds,",
  "sn11.15:5.3": "are not worth a sixteenth part",
  "sn11.15:5.4": "of a delightful human being.",
  "sn11.15:6.1": "Whether in village or wilderness,",
  "sn11.15:6.2": "in a valley or the uplands,",
  "sn11.15:6.3": "wherever the perfected ones live",
  "sn11.15:6.4": "is a delightful place.”"
}